          <strong>🇧🇬 New coalition government approved</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">After over two months of negotiations, Bulgaria has broken its <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-17-01-2025-br2-political-stalemate" target="_blank">political stalemate</a> by appointing a new prime minister, Rosen Zhelyazkov. He is from the center-right GERB party and was selected following the October elections, their seventh in three years. His government is supported by a broad coalition that includes leftist, populist, and centrist parties. Zhelyazkov thanked his coalition partners and stressed the government's priorities, mainly protecting the rule of law and ensuring Bulgaria's eventual adoption of the euro currency. Bulgaria has experienced significant political instability since 2020, including protests against oligarchic control of state institutions and allegations of vote-buying following recent elections.</p>
        </mj-text>
